    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1372">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/212.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Referring to the Department’s
                    note of yesterday regarding the expulsion of Spanish subjects from Torreon,
                    Mexico, I beg to inform you that the Department is in receipt of a telegram from
                    its representative at El Paso, Texas, stating [résumé of telegram from Special
                    Agent Carothers, dated April 7, 1914].</p>
                <p>Immediately upon receipt of the above message, the Department, late yesterday,
                    despatched a telegram to its representative at El Paso, in which he was
                    instructed [resume of telegram to Special Agent Carothers dated April 7,
                    1914].</p>
                <p>The Department will be glad to keep you informed of whatever additional
                    information is received from its representative in regard to this matter.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
